StoryBookPage.BodyText:
You pull a half-buried bottle from the sand; inside is a piece of paper. 

"A map." Ferensu leans over your shoulder. "There is Taz Al Jidda, Kushar... Az-Amakett." You recognize those landmarks, though what draws your attention is an island to the northwest, marked with an 'X.' There is a note on the back of the map; you read it out loud.

'It is Adallah of the Amakett who writes. Whoever finds this message, I charge you to bury my bones in accordance with the rites of the Drota. You will find them on the island I have marked;
